  <section class="content ">

    <div class="signup-wrapper">

      <section class="signup-form">
        <article class="form-container">

          <div class="title">1. INFORMATION ABOUT US AND HOW TO CONTACT US</div>
          <div class="content">These terms and conditions apply to your registration to and/or use of the BleeperBike
            bike sharing scheme provided by BleeperBike Ireland Opco Limited. BleeperBike Ireland Opco Limited is a
            company registered in Ireland. Our company registration number is 601088 and our registered office is at
            Temple Chambers 3 Burlington Road Dublin 4 D04RD68
          </div>
          <div class="content">Website: <a href="www.bleeperbike.com">www.bleeperbike.com</a></div>
          <div class="content">You can contact our customer service team by writing to us at
            <a href="mailto:sayhello@bleeperbike.com">sayhello@bleeperbike.com</a>. If we have to contact you we will
            communicate through the App or by writing to you.
          </div>


          <div class="title">2. TERMS WITH DEFINED MEANINGS</div>
          <div class="content">2.1 In the terms the following words have the following meanings:</div>
          <div class="content">App: means the BleeperBike app downloadable from the App Store and the Play Store.</div>
          <div class="content">Bike: means a bike made available for hire by BleeperBike.</div>
          <div class="content">Charges: the charges payable by you in respect of bike hire and any additional charges
            that may be payable in accordance with paragraphs 7 or 9 below. Registered User: refers to a person who has
            registered to use the BleeperBike service by providing us with certain personal and payment details when
            registering for an account with us.
          </div>
          <div class="content">We, our and us: refers to BleeperBike.</div>
          <div class="content">You, your: refers to a user of the BleeperBike service.</div>


          <div class="title">3. BleeperBike TERMS</div>
          <div class="content">3.1 These are the terms and conditions on which we offer bike hire and related products,
            services and digital content.
          </div>
          <div class="content">3.2 We reserve the right to refuse BleeperBike membership at our complete discretion.
          </div>
          <div class="content">3.3 Please read these terms carefully. These terms tell you who we are and more
            information about our services and the charges applicable.
          </div>
          <div class="content">3.4 You must be 18 or over to set up a BleeperBike account and hire a bike.</div>
          <div class="content">3.5 You agree that we will process all personal data in accordance with our
            <a href="privacyPolicy.html">Privacy Policy</a>.
          </div>
          <div class="content">3.6 We reserve the right to suspend your account at any time for your suspected failure
            to comply with these terms and conditions.
          </div>
          <div class="content">3.7 We may amend these terms and conditions, our Charges and details of the BleeperBike
            service from time to time. In these circumstances, you may be eligible for a refund of certain Charges that
            you have paid us in accordance with our refund policy.
          </div>
          <div class="content">3.8 No staff member other than a company director has authority to make individual
            exceptions or amendments to your contract with us.
          </div>
          <div class="content">3.9 We will always try to run a reliable service. Sometimes our bike hire service will be
            unable to operate for reasons beyond our reasonable control.
          </div>
          <div class="content">3.10 We offer no guarantee that a bike will be available when needed. All bike hire is
            subject to availability.
          </div>


          <div class="title">4. HIRING AND RETURNING BIKES</div>
          <div class="content">4.1 You may unlock a bike by scanning the QR code on the lock of the bike. If you are
            unable to scan the QR code successfully for whatever reason, you may alternatively enter the bikes
            identification number to unlock the bike. The bikes identification number is on both sides of the bike and
            starts with 17.
          </div>
          <div class="content">4.2 When you have finished riding the bike, you may park it at any of the recognised
            public cycle parking spaces identified on our map. If a bike is not parked in one of these identified spaces
            then it is either deemed mis-parked or lost. You must park your bike in a tidy, unobtrusive manner.
          </div>
          <div class="content">4.3 To park the bike, place it next to a bike rack, engage the lock and tap on End
            Journey on the App.
          </div>


          <div class="title">5. BIKE USAGE CHARGES</div>
          <div class="content">5.1 You must have a minimum of €1 credit on your e-wallet or have a valid membership to
            be able to unlock a bike.
          </div>
          <div class="content">5.2 We charge €1 per hour and €1 for each hour thereafter for our bike hire.</div>
          <div class="content">5.3 You need to provide a valid debit or credit card, which is either a VISA, Visa
            Electron, Mastercard or Amex and which is accepted by us and from which we can deduct the Charges.
          </div>
          <div class="content">5.4 During the period of you being a registered user, you agree not to cancel your
            payment card without first telling us and providing an alternative payment card from which we can collect
            the Charges.
          </div>
          <div class="content">5.5 BleeperBike bonus credit is not refundable.</div>


          <div class="title">6. MEMBERSHIPS</div>
          <div class="content">6.1 Memberships allow the member up to two rides a day and up to one hour each.</div>
          <div class="content">6.2 If you exceed this daily allowance as a member, you will be charged €1 per hour in
            accordance with our standard usage fee.
          </div>
          <div class="content">6.3 You may purchase a €5 Day Pass, which allows for 12 hours usage for €5.</div>
          <div class="content">6.4 The annual memberships and the Day Pass shall commence at the point of purchase.
          </div>
          <div class="content">6.5 The annual memberships and the Day Pass shall automatically expire at the end of the
            relevant period. Upon expiration, you continue to be a registered user and have the option to purchase
            another membership or Day Pass.
          </div>
          <div class="content">6.6 You may cancel your membership to the BleeperBike service at any time within 14 days
            of first becoming a member. If you cancel your membership early, we will deduct our fees for your use up to
            the point of cancellation, calculated on the basis of our standard €1 per hour fee. No refund will be given
            in respect of any cancellation after this 14 day period.
          </div>


          <div class="title">7. PERIOD OF USE</div>
          <div class="content">7.1 BleeperBike should not be used for more than 24 consecutive hours. 24 consecutive
            hours is the maximum period of use.
          </div>
          <div class="content">7.2 You must park and lock the BleeperBike at a recognised public cycle parking prior to
            the end of the maximum period of use.
          </div>
          <div class="content">7.3 The bike is deemed lost and Charges shall apply should the maximum period of use be
            exceeded.
          </div>


          <div class="title">8. BIKE FAULTS</div>
          <div class="content">8.1 We ask that you carry out a visual inspection of the bike before unlocking it. Also,
            if you discover any problems with the bike once unlocked, you have five minutes from unlocking to return it
            to a recognised parking area. If you report the fault to us using the App you will not be charged in this
            instance, provided the bike is returned within the five minute grace period.
          </div>


          <div class="title">9. USER OBLIGATIONS</div>
          <div class="content">9.1 You are responsible for keeping the bike safe at all times whilst it is in your
            possession or control.
          </div>
          <div class="content">9.2 You agree to use the bike safely and responsibly and in accordance with applicable
            laws and regulations including the Highway Code.
          </div>
          <div class="content">9.3 You shall comply with all policies we have in place from time to time regarding your
            bike hire and use of the BleeperBike service.
          </div>
          <div class="content">9.4 You are responsible for all items you transport on a bike.</div>
          <div class="content">9.5 You must return the bike in the same condition as when you unlocked it, except for
            fair wear and tear.
          </div>
          <div class="content">9.6 We may occasionally need you to provide us with information regarding your use of a
            bike. If requested, you agree to provide details of your full name and address and details of each specified
            bike hire, including in respect of your use of the bike and the route taken.
          </div>


          <div class="title">10. BIKE USAGE RESTRICTIONS</div>
          <div class="content">10.1 You must not:</div>
          <div class="content">10.1.1 allow any other person to ride the bike and you must not give a lift to any
            passengers, including animals;
          </div>
          <div class="content">10.1.2 tamper with, modify or attempt to disassemble the bike in any way and you must not
            add any accessories or other additions to the bike;
          </div>
          <div class="content">10.1.3 damage the bike;</div>
          <div class="content">10.1.4 lock the bike other than in accordance with BleeperBike instructions;</div>
          <div class="content">10.1.5 use a bike for any business purposes;</div>
          <div class="content">10.1.6 load the bike with a total weight of more than 120 kilograms;</div>
          <div class="content">10.1.7 carry any illegal or dangerous objects;</div>
          <div class="content">10.1.8 use the bike in a reckless or dangerous manner and you must not use the bike for
            any kind of stunts or ticks;
          </div>
          <div class="content">10.1.9 use the bike in connection with any illegal, immoral or disorderly conduct.</div>


          <div class="title">11. REFERRALS</div>
          <div class="content">11.1 If you refer BleeperBike to a friend who subscribes to an annual membership we will
            give you a one month extension on your membership or give you a one month membership if you are a pay as you
            go user.
          </div>
          <div class="content">11.2 If you refer BleeperBike to a friend who signs up for an account (including having
            registered a debit or credit card) you and your friend will each receive a €1 bonus credit.
          </div>


          <div class="title">12. INSURANCE</div>
          <div class="content">12.You are not insured by us to use Bleeperbikes and you do so entirely at your own risk.
            it is advised that you take out your own public liability insurance if you do not have such policy already
            in place.
          </div>


          <div class="title">13. OTHER CHARGES</div>
          <div class="content">13.1 If you damage a bike we will charge you a repair fee, payable on demand, of up to a
            maximum of €500.
          </div>
          <div class="content">13.2 If you lose a bike you shall immediately pay us €500.</div>
          <div class="content">13.3 You hereby authorise us to deduct these payment from the payment card registered to
            your BleeperBike account.
          </div>


          <div class="title">14. COMPLAINTS AND DISPUTES</div>
          <div class="content">14.1 Complaints and disputes are handled according to our Complaints Handling Policy. We
            have 14 days to reply to an initial complaint. You agree to provide us with any information we may request
            to help in our investigation.
          </div>
          <div class="content">14.2 These terms and conditions shall be governed by Irish Law.</div>
          <div class="content">14.3 If a dispute arises between you and us and you want to take court proceedings, you
            must do so at a court in the Republic of Ireland.
          </div>


          <div class="title">15. FURTHER INFORMATION</div>
          <div class="content">15.1 Only you and we have rights under these terms and conditions. No other person shall
            have any rights under these terms and conditions.
          </div>
          <div class="content">15.2 You may not transfer any of your rights under these terms and conditions to any
            other person.
          </div>

        </article>
